pullsbody:
Hello, please merge ASAP these suggestions to add from legal team.

(Here is the text I added: in case for any reason it appears in a strange way please feel free to edit formatting-)

The grand prize also includes the opportunity to have the winning game reviewed by Chillingo for possible publication on that site and by the Firefox Marketplace team who might feature it in the Firefox Marketplace. An internal review committee at each company will review the winning game and determine in the committee's sole discretion whether to publish or feature it. Winning the grand prize does not guarantee that the game will be published by Chillingo or featured in Firefox Marketplace. In order for the game to be eligible to be published by Chillingo the winning game must be a great title with consumer appeal and have the potential for commercial success. If Chillingo believes the winning title meets the criteria, Chillingo can decide whether or not to publish the game to HTML5 app stores and may also collaborate with the developer to port it to other platforms. The game must also be the sole creation of the developer, where Chillingo owns and the developer must be able to grant an exclusive license to Chillingo. Chillingo will require developers to sign a publishing agreement before it publishes the game. Chillingo reserves the right to determine whether or not to publish the one winning title from the Mozilla Game On competition. In order for the winning game to be in the Firefox Marketplace the game must meet the following criteria https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Apps/Marketplace_review_criteria and must comply with the Firefox Marketplace rules and policies which can be found at: https://marketplace.firefox.com/developers/docs/policies/agreement and https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Apps/Marketplace_review_criteria.

pulltitle: Flags for challenge being open, closed, not_started
pullsbody:
These should make things:
- easier to allow for the templates to break
- more control about how we show content dependent on the stage the challenge is in
pull_repo_desc: Simple playdoh site to  support the gameon 2012 challenge
pull_commit_message: Making the templates less easier to break by not having a challenge in the system - something that should only ever happen once but you never know

pullsbody: We can use this to control opening/close dates around the site, and also to highlight when the challenge is open and when it is closed.
